data.description: Beautiful El Camino rancher, located in one of Pueblo's desirable neighborhood. This stunning property has real hardwood floors, wood-framed, tinted-Anderson windows, fireplace in the living room. Granite counter top in the in-kitchen eating area. The house has a split bedroom design. The primary bathroom has a walk-in shower and a large soaker tub and two separate vanities. Main level laundry room for convenience, formal dining room area perfect for entertaining. The house is spacious, bright and airy with 9-foot ceilings and vaulted ceilings in the living room. The unfinished basement has 1814 square feet, plenty of room to finish with extra bedrooms and a family fun room. The basement has garden level windows, and a locked gun closet/tornado shelter. The back deck built with high performance, low maintenance Trex product. The backyard is fenced in from the greenbelt and has a TUFF shed for additional storage, perfect for garden tools. This area of El Camino has a neighborhood HOA that you can become a part of, only if the homeowner chooses to. Voluntary $50 a year.
